1D pass 1H pass 2H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "b250f5778fcdab04d3d22360290f49cba41e8a203bc57770ef14c6877c0af3b9"]
[Category "Basic Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "basic_bidding/minor_suit_openings"]
[Student "S"]
{Some might jump to 2NT, "to show partner my point count". Some might jump to 3\D, "to force partner to game and show my \D support". The wise ones will just bid 1\H, striving to find an 8-card Major fit, the first priority of bidding.

You choose the 1\H route, and partner obligingly says 2\H.  

Remember "She who knows, goes"? You know of the 8-card Major fit. You know of at least 26 combined points. You know you should bid 4\H, so you do.}

